00:07:31.780 --> 00:07:35.230
just arbitrary members
of the real numbers.

00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:38.070
This vector is just a bunch
of arbitrary real numbers.

00:07:38.070 --> 00:07:53.390
So for T to be onto, the span of
a1, a2, all the way to an,

00:07:53.390 --> 00:07:59.270
has to be equal to Rm, has to
be equal to your co-domain.

00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:02.100
That just means that you can
achieve any vector in your

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:04.190
co-domain with the linear
combinations of the column

00:08:04.190 --> 00:08:05.270
vectors of this.

00:08:05.270 --> 00:08:08.590
What's the span of a matrices'
column vectors?

00:08:08.590 --> 00:08:12.450
By definition that is the
matrices' column space.

00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:15.910
So we could say, that means that
the span of these guys

00:08:15.910 --> 00:08:18.725
have to be Rn, or another way
